TY  - JOUR
T1  - Nonparametric Estimation of the Cumulative Intensity Function for a Nonhomogeneous Poisson Process from Overlapping Realizations
AU  - Arkin, Bradford L.
AU  - Leemis, Lawrence M.
Y1  - 2000/07/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.46.7.989.12037
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.46.7.989.12037
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 989
EP  - 998
VL  - 46
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A nonparametric technique for estimating the cumulative intensity function of a nonhomogeneous Poisson process from one or more realizations on an interval is extended here to include realizations that overlap. This technique does not require any arbitrary parameters from the modeler, and the estimated cumulative intensity function can be used to generate a point process for simulation by inversion.
AB  - A nonparametric technique for estimating the cumulative intensity function of a nonhomogeneous Poisson process from one or more realizations on an interval is extended here to include realizations that overlap. This technique does not require any arbitrary parameters from the modeler, and the estimated cumulative intensity function can be used to generate a point process for simulation by inversion.
